      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Cross-study hemolysis model synthesis — power-law exponent range",
      "description": "A synthesis of multiple prior studies examining power-law hemolysis model coefficients (Giersiepen, Zhang, Taskin, and Arora formulations) across centrifugal and axial pump geometries. The synthesized exponent range (alpha: 0.62–0.77, beta: 1.99–2.42) was used to bound model-form uncertainty in the CFD hemolysis predictions. This node consolidates findings from seven independent experimental campaigns spanning 1990–2019 and provides the epistemic uncertainty envelope applied in the sensitivity analysis. The synthesis is considered authoritative for Class II CPB device assessments at MRL 2 and has been reviewed by the credibility assessment team."
    }
